        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="de/d6d/structsgns_1_1primitives_1_1_version" kindref="compound">Version</ref> of the implementation of the specification. Nodes are free to ignore this; it serves only as an indication that the code is different; as long as the other two versions are the same then while the actual code may be different, it is nonetheless required to do the same thing. Non-verification-breaking optimizations are about the only changes that could be made which would result in only the impl_version changing. <ref refid="de/d6d/structsgns_1_1primitives_1_1_version" kindref="compound">Version</ref> of the runtime specification. A full-node will not attempt to use its native runtime in substitute for the on-chain Wasm runtime unless all of <computeroutput><ref refid="de/d6d/structsgns_1_1primitives_1_1_version_1a61c3cd1fd166e6fb1134171e934d097b" kindref="member">spec_name</ref></computeroutput>, <computeroutput><ref refid="de/d6d/structsgns_1_1primitives_1_1_version_1a7ef5be03790801aab1bdeb84b5fc38ae" kindref="member">spec_version</ref></computeroutput> and <computeroutput><ref refid="de/d6d/structsgns_1_1primitives_1_1_version_1a89b6213d88c67b3dd6963132f9d41b47" kindref="member">authoring_version</ref></computeroutput> are the same between Wasm and native. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
