    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Runtime version. This should not be thought of as classic Semver (major/minor/tiny). This triplet have different semantics and mis-interpretation could cause problems. In particular: bug fixes should result in an increment of <computeroutput><ref refid="de/d6d/structsgns_1_1primitives_1_1_version_1a7ef5be03790801aab1bdeb84b5fc38ae" kindref="member">spec_version</ref></computeroutput> and possibly <computeroutput><ref refid="de/d6d/structsgns_1_1primitives_1_1_version_1a89b6213d88c67b3dd6963132f9d41b47" kindref="member">authoring_version</ref></computeroutput>, absolutely not <computeroutput><ref refid="de/d6d/structsgns_1_1primitives_1_1_version_1abffbefdd753ad2011c4abdc2dc3708a5" kindref="member">impl_version</ref></computeroutput> since they change the semantics of the runtime. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
